cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 90 miles west of Camagüey, Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: Expected to turn north-northwest later today, cross the Florida Straits, pass near or over the Florida Keys tonight, then move into the southeastern Gulf of Mexico while bending westward
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: near or over the Florida Keys (Upper Keys / Florida Bay)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Hurricane and storm-surge watches are confined to South Florida coast from Deerfield Beach to Bonita Beach, including the Florida Keys
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical-storm warnings for central and South Florida peninsula, Florida Keys, parts of Cuba and NW Bahamas
weather_observation.impacted_coast: South-central Cuba, the Florida Keys, South and Southwest Florida coast, and eventually portions of the eastern Gulf of Mexico shoreline; minor surge expected northward to Altamaha Sound GA
weather_observation.wind: Low chance (≤8%) of tropical-storm-force winds reaching the port late week; breezy onshore flow possible
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor coastal inundation of 2–3 ft above ground possible Monday–Tuesday from Altamaha Sound southward, including Brunswick’s barrier islands
weather_observation.rainfall: Periods of moderate to locally heavy rain (1–3 in.) possible mid-week as Eta’s moisture streams northward
weather_observation.other_hazards: Dangerous surf and rip currents along the Georgia barrier-island beaches beginning early week
